      "content": "small changes dont really matter though. like, what's the point of recycling or \"finding purpose\" when the biosphere is collapsing? it feels like trying to put out a forest fire with a water pistol. it just feels dishonest to keep pretending that living a little life matters when the whole system is fundamentally broken. it's hard to see any logic in just sticking around to watch it all burn.",
